    <div class="recipe-card">
        <h2 class="recipe-title">Spaghetti Carbonara</h2>
        <p class="recipe-description">A classic Italian pasta dish with eggs, cheese, and pancetta.</p>
        <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
        <ul class="ingredients">
            <li>8 oz spaghetti</li>
            <li>2 large eggs</li>
            <li>1 cup grated Pecorino Romano cheese</li>
            <li>2 oz pancetta</li>
            <li>2 cloves garlic</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper to taste</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Instructions:</h3>
        <ol class="instructions">
            <li>Cook the spaghetti according to package instructions.</li>
            <li>In a bowl, whisk together eggs and grated cheese.</li>
            <li>In a pan, saut√© pancetta and garlic until crispy.</li>
            <li>Combine cooked spaghetti, egg mixture, and pancetta. Toss until creamy.</li>
            <li>Season with salt and black pepper. Serve hot.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
